Class MyMap<K,V>

java.lang.Object
com.dnikitin.map.MyMap<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type of keys maintained by this map
V - the type of mapped values
All Implemented Interfaces:
Map<K,V>, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
public class MyMap<K,V> extends Object implements Map<K,V>, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
An AVL-Tree-based implementation of the Map interface.

This map provides guaranteed O(log n) time cost for the contains, get, put, and remove operations.

The map is sorted according to the natural ordering of its keys (if keys implement Comparable), or by a Comparator provided at map creation time.

    • MyMap

      public MyMap()
      Constructs a new, empty tree map, ordered according to the natural ordering of its keys.

      All keys inserted into the map must implement the Comparable interface.

    • MyMap

      public MyMap(Map<? extends K, ? extends V> m)
      Constructs a new map containing the same mappings as the specified map.

      The new map will be ordered according to the natural ordering of its keys. All keys inserted into the new map must implement the Comparable interface.

      This constructor iterates over the given map's entry set and inserts each mapping into this map, which results in an O(N log N) runtime, where N is the number of entries in the given map.

      Parameters:
      m - the map whose mappings are to be placed in this map
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the specified map or any of its keys or values are null
      ClassCastException - if any key in m does not implement Comparable
